quote_first: But it wasn't going on! It was two-thirty-four, well.
quote_last: and nothing had happened. Suppose he got a room call, or the elevator night-bell rang, now.
quote_raw: But it wasn't going on! It was two-thirty-four, well. Two-thirty-three and nothing had happened. Suppose he got a room call, or the elevator night-bell rang, now.
title: A Swell-looking Babe
author: Jim Thompson
